      <h1>AI</h1>
      <h4>Author Name: Angel F. Smith</h4>
    </header>
    <main>
      <p>
        <strong>Introduction:</strong> Artificial Intelligence (AI) refers to the development of computer systems capable of performing tasks that typically require human intelligence, such as learning, reasoning, problem-solving, and understanding natural language. Its relevance is increasingly evident across various sectors, where AI technologies are enhancing efficiency, accuracy, and innovation.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Fact 1:</strong> In healthcare, AI is revolutionizing patient care and operational processes. For example, Neurofit, a New York City-based startup, combines neuroscience with AI to develop an app that addresses chronic stress by analyzing users' stress profiles using biometric data, delivering personalized guidance. Additionally, companies like Grove AI and Infinitus Systems are creating AI agents to handle administrative tasks such as registering participants for clinical trials and automating post-discharge patient follow-ups, thereby reducing physician burnout and improving workflow efficiency.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Fact 2:</strong> In business, AI enhances customer experience and operational efficiency. Daily Harvest, a meal delivery service, utilizes AI to analyze customer orders and browsing history, providing personalized product recommendations and preventing customer fatigue with their food offerings. Moreover, Microsoft's Dragon Copilot serves as an AI assistant in healthcare, automating documentation tasks and providing reliable medical information, thus alleviating clinicians' administrative burdens and allowing them to focus more on patient care. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Fact 3:</strong> In transportation, AI facilitates the development of autonomous vehicles, enhancing road safety and efficiency. Companies like Tesla and Waymo are advancing self-driving technologies that rely on AI to interpret sensor data and make real-time driving decisions. These systems aim to reduce accidents caused by human error and improve traffic flow. Additionally, AI-driven cloud robotics enable autonomous delivery drones and vehicles, optimizing logistics and supply chain operations. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Conclusion:</strong> AI's integration into healthcare, business, and transportation sectors underscores its transformative impact on modern society. By automating complex tasks, personalizing services, and enhancing decision-making processes, AI contributes to improved outcomes and operational efficiencies across various industries. As AI technologies continue to evolve, their potential to drive innovation and address complex challenges is immense, highlighting the need for thoughtful integration and ethical considerations.
      </p>
